parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to shut down while in motion, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle suddenly goes dark
losing all electrical function
and shuts off in the middle of traffic. The issue is intermittent and can occur randomly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the window motor can cause inconvenience and discomfort for the driver and passengers.
symptoms: The driver-side window randomly stops working
despite the motor and switches being tested and functioning correctly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the backup camera can increase the risk of accidents, as the driver may not be able to see obstacles behind the vehicle.
symptoms: The backup camera image appears upside down
with flashing or red and green stripes. The issue can occur randomly and persist even after the vehicle is turned off.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag system can increase the risk of injury or fatality in the event of a collision.
symptoms: The airbags do not deploy in the event of a collision
despite the vehicle being severely damaged.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the keyless entry system can cause inconvenience and disrupt the normal operation of the vehicle.
symptoms: The vehicle's dashboard displays a warning that the key is not in the vehicle
despite the key being present. The issue can cause the vehicle to shut down and not restart until some time has passed.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine and Electronic Throttle Control Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the engine and electronic throttle control can cause the vehicle to lose power and speed, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The check engine
ESC
and electronic throttle control warning lights come on
and the vehicle bogs down
unable to exceed 40 mph. The issue can occur repeatedly and may not be resolved despite multiple visits to the dealership.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the backup camera can cause difficulty or impossibility to back up safely, increasing the risk of accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The backup camera displays a black screen
a series of colors with no image
or an upside-down or blurry image
making it hard to see what's behind the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unintended rollaway of the vehicle can cause accidents or injuries, especially on hills or inclines.
symptoms: The vehicle shuts off on its own while in drive
and the brakes do not respond
forcing the driver to shift into park to stop the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Burning Smell of Fluid, Plastic, or Metal
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The burning smell of fluid, plastic, or metal can indicate a potential fire hazard or engine failure, which can cause accidents or injuries.
symptoms: A burning smell is present while driving the car
indicating a possible issue with the engine or electrical system.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Uconnect infotainment system can cause frustration and distraction while driving, potentially leading to accidents.
symptoms: The Uconnect system does not work half the time
and the dealer and manufacturer blame each other for the issue.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The misfiring of the front cylinder head can cause decreased engine performance, reduced fuel efficiency, and potentially lead to more severe engine damage if left unaddressed.
symptoms: Engine misfire
decreased engine performance
reduced fuel efficiency.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission clunking and slipping can cause damage to the transmission, leading to costly repairs and potentially causing accidents due to loss of control.
symptoms: Clunking or banging noise when shifting from reverse to drive
transmission slipping
vibration or shaking
unstable speeds
engine struggling to accelerate.
